  "text": "Calcium channel blockers, in addition to reducing In and twitch by reducing calcium load' (cf. [CITATION_1] , should have added efficacy if they reduce action potential duration. These additional actions result from the effects that membrane potential (i.e., action potential duration) has on net calcium entry across the sarcolemma and on calcium released from the sarcoplasmic reticulum.",
